    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "One good idea is worth a week of posts.\n\nMost of it never gets made, because rewriting it five ways for five platforms is a grind.\n\nThis automation does the rewriting and the scheduling. One piece in, a week out.\n\nHere are the 7 steps to build it: https://t.co/Mafh27RTea",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2064969637713097163",
    "time": "2026-06-11 15:15",
    "created_at": "Thu Jun 11 07:15:01 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2064969637713097163",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "1. The Trigger\n\nDecide what starts the run. A new doc in a folder, a finished transcript, a tagged note.\n\nExample: drop a finished blog post into a Drive folder and the workflow fires automatically. No button to press.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2064969650157547557",
    "time": "2026-06-11 15:15",
    "created_at": "Thu Jun 11 07:15:04 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2064969650157547557",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "2. The Extractor\n\nThe first AI step reads the long piece and pulls the core ideas, quotes, and stats worth reusing.\n\nExample: a 1,500-word post becomes a clean list of 8 standalone points, each strong enough to anchor its own post.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2064969662362968092",
    "time": "2026-06-11 15:15",
    "created_at": "Thu Jun 11 07:15:07 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2064969662362968092",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "3. The Repurposer\n\nThe next step turns each point into platform-native drafts. Same idea, different shape per channel.\n\nExample: one point becomes an X thread opener, a LinkedIn post, and a short newsletter blurb, each written for how that platform reads.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2064969674358718955",
    "time": "2026-06-11 15:15",
    "created_at": "Thu Jun 11 07:15:10 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2064969674358718955",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "4. The Visual Brief\n\nFor any post that needs an image, the workflow drafts the image prompt or design spec next to the copy.\n\nExample: a stat post comes out with a ready-to-paste prompt for the chart or quote card that goes with it.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2064969686371221833",
    "time": "2026-06-11 15:15",
    "created_at": "Thu Jun 11 07:15:13 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2064969686371221833",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "5. The Review Gate\n\nEvery draft lands in one place for you to approve, edit, or kill before anything goes out. The human stays in the loop.\n\nExample: drafts drop into a Notion board or a spreadsheet, one row each, with an approve checkbox.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2064969698459160996",
    "time": "2026-06-11 15:15",
    "created_at": "Thu Jun 11 07:15:16 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2064969698459160996",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "6. The Scheduler\n\nApproved posts get pushed straight to your publishing tool and slotted into the calendar.\n\nExample: a checked row sends the post to Typefully or Buffer and schedules it for the next open slot.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2064969710509387933",
    "time": "2026-06-11 15:15",
    "created_at": "Thu Jun 11 07:15:18 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2064969710509387933",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "7. The Feedback Loop\n\nAfter posts go live, the workflow logs what each one did so the next run learns what to make more of.\n\nExample: likes and impressions get written back next to each post, so you can see which angles earned their slot.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2064969722685501645",
    "time": "2026-06-11 15:15",
    "created_at": "Thu Jun 11 07:15:21 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2064969722685501645",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "Build this once in n8n, Make, or Zapier and one idea turns into a week of posts, without rewriting it five ways yourself.\n\nYou still approve every draft before it ships.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2064969734689579015",
    "time": "2026-06-11 15:15",
    "created_at": "Thu Jun 11 07:15:24 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2064969734689579015",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
